# 📚 Arrays in Java

Welcome to the **Arrays** section of my Java DSA Journey!

This folder contains my complete learning journey for arrays in Java, starting from the fundamentals and progressing to problem-solving and algorithmic thinking.

Throughout this section, I explore the core concepts of arrays by writing programs, solving practice questions, and implementing common algorithms. Each program is created to strengthen my understanding of how arrays work and how they are used in Data Structures and Algorithms.

## 🎯 What You'll Find

* Array fundamentals
* Array declaration and initialization
* Input and output operations
* Indexing and traversal
* Updating array elements
* Default values
* Array length and indexing concepts
* Exception handling with arrays
* Beginner to intermediate array problems
* Searching and sorting algorithms (added as I progress)

## 🚀 Purpose

The goal of this section is to build a strong foundation in arrays before moving on to more advanced data structures and algorithms. Every program in this folder represents a step in my learning journey and reflects my effort to understand concepts through hands-on coding rather than memorization.

Thank you for visiting my repository. I hope my learning journey is helpful to other beginners exploring Java and DSA.
